Tamil Nadu
Nov 07, 2014
Abuse
Description:
			An history sheeter, allegedly been engaged in prostitution, has been detained under the Goondas Act and two women rescued from his custody.

On specific information, police conducted a raid in Chetpet area, arrested Davidraj and rescued the two women.

Investigations revealed that Davidraj had been arrested for the third time this year alone on charges of pushing women into flesh trade and hence was detained under the stringent Goondas Act and lodged in the central prison at Puzhal, they said.

The two women have been sent to government home at Mylapore, police added.


